<TEXT>
when american adventurer william 
walker set fire to this handsome colonial city in 1856 the 
citizens are said to have hidden their gold in holes in the ground 
or in thick adobe walls 
among the remnants of that episode is the granadinos tendency 
to tap on walls hoping for a hollow sound and the memory of the 
us invader who stuck a sign in the smoldering ruins with a 
cynical message here was granada 
when he came here for a campaign rally president daniel ortega 
seized on that 133yearold memory to drive home one of the 
sandinistas messages they represent the defense of national 
sovereignty in the face of us intervention 
times havent changed that much ortega told some 6000 
granadinos who recently gathered at the central park for a rally 
the yankees are still trying 
in one campaign appearance after another ortega plays the 
sandinistas top drawing cards patriotism patronage and 
packaging he is taking aim at two important blocs as he tries for 
another sixyear term in the feb 25 elections women and youth 
this is a young country the young people are the future they 
are our future said one sandinista militant whose job is to 
observe rallies 
the voting age in nicaragua is 16 and an estimated 46 percent 
of nicaraguans are under 15 years of age 
women especially those in the 1635 age bracket are also an 
important bloc they normally are 51 percent of the population but 
are an even greater percentage now more than 12 years of armed 
conflict has killed thousands of men and left others refugees or 
members of the contra army ranks 
early in the campaign ortega a younglooking 44 was 
repackaged to create a new image 
daniel president of the young proclaim posters billboards 
and grafitti many of them around university campuses and schools 
the president traded his prescription glasses for contact 
lenses he switched from his sober trademark camouflage uniform to 
black tshirts worn under cotton bomber jackets with sleeves rolled 
up he started wearing cowboy boots 
in december ortega started dancing with skimpily clad beauty 
queens 
in granada he danced on stage with marucha a barefoot and 
aproned food vendor known for her chancho con yuca a favorite 
nicaraguan dish of fried pork rinds with yucca the crowd was 
delighted 
a regular feature at sandinista rallies is a session where 
ortega poses with children for photographs 
dourfaced state security agents lean down from the 7foothigh 
speaking platform to pick up tiny babies whose parents want to go 
home with an instant picture of junior and the president 
like most rallies the granada rally was followed by a ceremony 
honoring relatives of war victims 
this time it was a dinner at granadas best hotel for members of 
the mothers of heroes and martyrs a sandinista organization with 
few nicaraguan families untouched by the war between the 
sandinistas and the usbacked contra rebels and with most people 
unable to afford restaurants the gesture will likely be remembered 
josefa salinas the 22yearold daughter of a poor peasant 
family waited in a broiling sun then a downpour for ortega to 
appear 
ms salinas from the nearby community of el capulin graduated 
in december from a granada technical school with a degree in 
accounting 
before i would not have been able to study before you had 
to pay now its free she said 
ms salinas was 12 years old when the sandinistas came to power 
in july 1979 and ousted dictator anastasio somoza 
the irony is that while the sandinistas have made it possible 
for a poor peasant child such as ms salinas to obtain an 
education now that she has it she cant find work unemployment 
among nicaraguan youth is widespread and unabating 
im looking but there doesnt seem to be any work she said 
however her vote will be 100 percent totally for the 
sandinista front 
why 
its the way they are carrying out the revolutionary process 
how they treat the people she said before with the 
somocistas the government would deal only with the rich people and 
the gringos just among themselves now we are taken into account 
ms salinas father was an itinerant peasant who rented his 
labor to large landowners under somoza the sandinista government 
gave him land through agrarian reform and he now works in a farm 
cooperative 
the sandinistas have exercised their patronage as the ruling 
party and handed out hundreds of land and home titles to nicaraguan 
families theyve given taxi cooperatives easy credit to buy new 
cars government workers have obtained pay raises 
party pins and other symbols of recognition have been 
distributed like candy as have tshirts baseball caps tote bags 
belt buckles kerchiefs pens cigarette lighters and posters 
the sandinista youth an organization for men and women roughly 
between ages 15 and 30 harnesses that force for party purposes 
the government sponsors popular dances with local and foreign bands 
and promotes sports belonging to it means preferential treatment 
in obtaining scholarships and other advantages 
high school student marta lorena mendoza 18 said she joined 
the sandinista youth four days before the rally and had been sent 
out everyday to hand out leaflets announcing ortegas arrival 
everybody in the neighborhood belongs to the sandinista 
youth she said my cousin an older boy who is in the 
sandinista army told me i should join 
