<TEXT>
panamanians have gone on a spree of 
witch hunts in the political shakeup following the us invasion 
sometimes using american troops to settle personal vendettas us 
army and panamanian sources say 
the persistent accusations dismissals of public employees and 
charges made in the news media are hindering the organization of 
president guillermo endaras new government frustrating american 
officials and delaying the removal of us forces according to the 
sources 
everyone has turned into a squealer said army col charles 
morris director of a 200member special group called in to help 
the new government organize itself 
they have gone wild said another us army source on 
condition of anonymity they are using the us army for their 
own personal revenge we get calls from someone saying there are 
weapons in some house and we have to check it 
shortly after the dec 20 invasion toppled gen manuel antonio 
noriega the us army began acting as a police force for the new 
government 
american forces have arrested not only former members of 
noriegas high command but leftists and leaders of old political 
parties including the leftist democratic revolutionary party that 
backed the old government 
as of friday the us army still held 100 military and civilian 
prisoners at fort clayton at the request of the panamanian 
government which was sorting out possible charges against some 
of them 
newspapers have become a daily register of purported wrongdoings 
by government officials business leaders and politicians who once 
had some tie to noriega 
us soldiers often following tips from neighbors or 
ideological foes arrested many members of leftist political 
parties and held them for two or three days in some cases their 
main sin was militancy in the communist party 
the soldiers would come in and arrest someone or they would 
go into an office and take what they wanted said mario rognoni 
who spent three days in custody because he served in government 
under noriega then they would encourage people to loot the place 
so they could blame the sacking on them 
the army took our computer our records and then left it open 
so people could take everything else alleged rognoni a 
democratic revolutionary party leader 
the retaliation has even extended to the girlfriends and 
mistresses of pronoriega officials who have had sofas cars and 
even dishes seized on the assumption they were bought with stolen 
money 
leaders of the new political opposition claim more than 8000 
public employees have been fired after they were accused of having 
been loyal to the past regime 
but many of the public employees were forced by the noriega 
government to participate in progovernment demonstrations or join 
the paramilitary groups it was either that or lose their jobs 
said a former member of a paramilitary organization what were 
you supposed to do when you have a family to feed 
the endara government has seized at least 10 radio stations and 
two television stations owned by people suspected of association 
with noriega 
more than 100 official accusations or private lawsuits filed 
against former government officials have piled up at the attorney 
generals office all must be investigated said attorney general 
rogelio cruz 
meanwhile the two competing newspapers la estrella and el 
siglo have been trying to outdo each other showing how close to 
noriega the others director was 
there is hatred there is desire for revenge the country has 
gone mad said rognoni 
the worst part said a politician who spoke on condition of 
anonymity is that the new ins who now own this country did not 
fight for it 
the gringos gave it to them on a silver platter they did not 
shed a single drop of blood for it 
</TEXT>
