twothirds of the embassies the white house personnel director 
said sunday 
for the next three years of bushs term close to 100 
percent of ambassadorial appointments will go to career foreign 
service officers in order to maintain that balance of twothirds 
career officers onethird outside appointees charles g 
untermeyer said 
henceforth for the rest of the first bush term i expect 
very very few noncareer nominations the director of 
