an israeli army colonel was killed sunday 
in a gunbattle with guerrillas who staged an attack in israels 
selfdesignated security zone in south lebanon security 
sources reported 
the sources speaking on condition of anonymity said the 
attackers seized a house at 4 pm in the village of yaroun about 
one mile north of the israeli border 
israeli troops surrounded the building and the colonel was 
fatally wounded in a shootout the sources reported 
they said the identity of the raiders could not be determined 
and there were no further details about the clash it was not known 
whose house the guerrillas seized 
the guerrillas struck two days after israeli warplanes rocketed 
a palestinian radio station in the mieh mieh refugee camp in sidon 
and bases of the iranianbacked shiite moslem hezbollah or party 
of god in the highlands east of the city 
seven people were killed and 18 wounded in the raids the first 
israeli air strikes against targets in lebanon this year the raids 
are usually launched as reprisals for guerrilla attacks 
israel carved out the security zone in south lebanon in 1985 
when it withdrew the bulk of its occupation army three years after 
invading lebanon 
the enclave is patrolled by an estimated 1500 israeli troops 
and the south lebanon army a predominantly christian militia with 
an estimated 3000 fighters trained funded and equipped by israel 
the officer killed sunday was the highestranking israeli army 
officer killed in lebanon since the end of the lebanon invasion 
last year two israeli soldiers and 12 fighters of the south 
lebanon army were killed in clashes and attacks by palestinian and 
shiite moslem guerrillas in south lebanon the israeli military 
command says 
it lists nine guerrilla attempts to infiltrate into israel from 
lebanon last year along with 22 clashes between the lebanese 
guerrillas and israeli army or south lebanon army forces in these 
fights a total of 75 guerrillas have been killed and 12 captured 
