<TEXT>
from stella dallas to the thorn 
birds barbara stanwyck won enduring fame with her portrayals of 
steadfast strongwilled women she played variations of that role 
for most of her 82 years 
the actress who died of congestive heart failure saturday left 
an unforgettable gallery of portrayals the guntoting annie 
oakley the sharpie who conned henry fonda in the lady eve 
gary coopers promoter in meet john doe the wife who persuades 
fred macmurray to kill her husband in double indemnity 
the film titles tell the story the miracle woman 1931 
gambling lady 1934 the woman in red 1935 the bride 
walks out 1936 the mad miss manton 1938 lady of 
burlesque 1943 the lady gambles 1949 cattle queen of 
montana with ronald reagan 1954 the maverick queen 1956 
her television roles were also powerful the head of a ranching 
clan in the big valley the australian matriarch in the thorn 
birds and the imperious constance colby in the colbys 
miss stanwyck born ruby stevens learned survival as an orphan 
in new york citys brooklyn she was moved from one foster family 
to another and remarked in one of her last interviews i was 
always the kitchen maid cleaning up after the meals thats why i 
never learned to cook 
hoofing in nightclubs provided more lessons in how to survive 
and established her lifelong professionalism 
i was always afraid of being fired she said when you 
come from where i did and you can be fired at any minute this was 
before unions and you were responsible to feed and clothe 
yourself then you learn to be professional 
miss stanwyck carried those lessons into her film work she was 
adored by film crews who called her missy 
i think its a matter of caring about people i care about the 
crew she explained these people are my friends they help me 
im with them more than i am with anyone else if they are 
happy and contented the set is good i cant work under pressure 
and duress 
the actress had two marriages and both ended unhappily 
she married frank fay when he was the greatest emcee in 
vaudeville and she was a littleknown broadway actress newly named 
barbara stanwyck both were brought to hollywood during the talkie 
period and her career zoomed while his faded the marriage ended 
in 1935 
barbara stanwyck and robert taylor became one of hollywoods 
storybook marriages but it ended in 1951 friends believed she 
never fell out of love with the handsome actor 
miss stanwyck never remarried i never came close 
the actress seemed to withdraw in her later years her career 
was the only focus of her life and when the roles grew scarce she 
became almost a recluse seeing only close friends like jane wyman 
and nancy sinatra 
although miss stanwyck was nominated for an academy award four 
times the oscar eluded her until 1982 when she was presented with 
an honorary one for her career 
in her acceptance speech she thanked her fellow workers in the 
studios and added a few years ago i stood on this stage with 
william holden as a presenter i loved him very much and i miss 
him he always wished that i would get an oscar and so tonight my 
golden boy you got your wish 
miss stanwyck had helped holden through his first starring role 
in the 1939 movie golden boy they remained fast friends until 
his death in 1981 and every year he sent her a bouquet of roses on 
april 1 the day they started filming golden boy 
